# 3D Effect Prototype

## Overview
This project demonstrates a **3D visual effect** designed and prototyped using Figma. The interface creates a sense of depth and spatial interaction by applying perspective, layered elements, and motion-based transitions to simulate a three-dimensional experience within a 2D design environment.

## About the Project
The prototype explores how 3D-inspired UI design can enhance visual engagement and make interfaces feel more interactive and modern. By using perspective layouts, shadows, scaling, and prototype animations, the design mimics real-world depth and movement without requiring code.

3D UI effects help present interfaces in a more realistic and immersive way, improving storytelling and user perception of hierarchy and focus within a design. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

## Features
- 3D perspective-based layout
- Depth simulation using layered elements
- Interactive prototype transitions
- Motion-driven visual experience
- High-fidelity Figma prototyping

